类 Person

java.lang.Object
person.Person
public class Person extends Object
从以下版本开始:
March 26th, 2022 The class Person includes a enum type Gender with two values in it (MALE and FEMALE) The constructor will initialize the five instance variables in the class, which are the Person's surname (String), givenName (String), occupation (String), gender (Gender), and year of birth (int). It also includes a method called toString that will convert the object into a readable format to the standard output At last, Person class has a method called sameAs that will compares whether the attributes of two Person classes are the same
